b"@MoatsLikeKodak @Tyler_Barrett9 @abdullaefakhro @retaox @Logos_LP @lhamtil BUT, I would say at this multiple, the market is already discounting some of these factors into $HII stocks. It's undoubtedly cheap, but when I look at the opportunity cost of this vs. $NOC, $LMT, $MRCY, $LHX, I prefer to deploy my capital to those rather than $HII"

b"@MoatsLikeKodak @Tyler_Barrett9 @abdullaefakhro @retaox @Logos_LP @lhamtil The question is, do you want to hold $HII stock if the USN decides to deprioritize carriers? Even if the actual revenue decline would take decades, $HII would be stock with a no-growth segment that the will have to supplant with other growth drivers. It's a tall order."

b'@retaox @Tyler_Barrett9 @abdullaefakhro @MoatsLikeKodak @Logos_LP @lhamtil No one else can really make carriers, $HII dominates. They can also build smaller flat-tops (LHA is basically a mini-carrier, and DoD has expressed interest in buying more of those). If big carriers go away, 35% of $HII revenues are at risk.'

b'@abdullaefakhro @Chariot_Invest @retaox @MoatsLikeKodak @Logos_LP @lhamtil @Chariot_Invest just read your $HII blog. That\xe2\x80\x99s some nice work. Got your point across well for a shorter piece.'

b"@Tyler_Barrett9 @abdullaefakhro @retaox @MoatsLikeKodak @Logos_LP @lhamtil IMO, $HII has a lot of unknowns re: trajectory of major ship builds which they specialize in. Lots of talk about getting rid of carriers for other types of ships. If you can get comfortable with that risk, the stock is cheap, otherwise it's a trap."

b"@abdullaefakhro @Tyler_Barrett9 @MoatsLikeKodak @Logos_LP @lhamtil Losing frigate is a true bummer.

This is how I think about this :
They have contracts in pipeline for to keep them busy in the medium term.

In the long term, it's in Navy's best interest to give business to $HII. They can't pull this stunt again or it would cost them dearly."

b"@retaox @Tyler_Barrett9 @MoatsLikeKodak @Logos_LP @lhamtil this yr $HII lost frigate contract award to Italy's Fincantieri - unexpected and a shocker I must say). They have a strong position in the Columbia and Virginia class subs but that is shared with $GD, to whom they act as a subcontractor"

b'@retaox @Tyler_Barrett9 @MoatsLikeKodak @Logos_LP @lhamtil Concerns are not strictly limited to margins. There are valid questions re: fleet expansion strategy of the Navy (if autonomous-heavy $HII not best positioned for), less focus on large carriers, increased willingness of Navy to introduce more competition (earlier'
